1
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:38,565
Don't be nervous.

2
00:01:38,965 --> 00:01:40,066
We're going to give you anesthesia now.

3
00:02:03,223 --> 00:02:05,158
Begin circumferential pulmonary vein isolation.

4
00:02:05,492 --> 00:02:07,293
Set power to 40 watts.

5
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:08,928
Temperature, 52 degrees.

6
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:10,597
Thirty seconds per point.

7
00:02:10,997 --> 00:02:11,431
Copy.

8
00:02:14,767 --> 00:02:15,902
Check isolation.

9
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:18,271
Left upper pulmonary vein isolated.

10
00:02:18,838 --> 00:02:19,973
Left lower pulmonary vein isolated.

11
00:02:20,673 --> 00:02:22,041
Right upper pulmonary vein isolated.

12
00:02:22,675 --> 00:02:23,910
Right lower pulmonary vein isolated.

13
00:02:24,677 --> 00:02:26,146
Pacing confirms bidirectional block.

14
00:02:26,546 --> 00:02:27,480
No residual potentials.

15
00:02:27,847 --> 00:02:28,248
Success.

16
00:02:30,283 --> 00:02:31,651
Director Zhou, she's all yours.

17
00:02:31,851 --> 00:02:32,152
Thanks.

18
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:48,768
Hold this.

19
00:02:49,235 --> 00:02:50,003
Secure the guidewire.

20
00:02:58,411 --> 00:02:58,845
Continue.

21
00:02:59,546 --> 00:03:00,013
Okay.

22
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:38,885
Maximum left atrial appendage ostium diameter:

23
00:03:39,185 --> 00:03:40,053
28 millimeters.

24
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,988
Maximum landing zone diameter: 20 millimeters.

25
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:43,289
A 24-to-30 should work.

26
00:03:43,923 --> 00:03:44,324
Okay.

27
00:03:47,927 --> 00:03:49,395
24-to-30 left atrial appendage occluder.

28
00:03:49,862 --> 00:03:50,263
Confirmed.

29
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:34,507
Occluder in position.

30
00:04:35,408 --> 00:04:36,042
The position looks good.

31
00:04:36,276 --> 00:04:37,443
Fixation and seal are good too.

32
00:04:37,810 --> 00:04:38,645
No residual shunt.

33
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:41,948
Director, steady as ever.

34
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:44,150
You young people

35
00:04:44,384 --> 00:04:45,718
should learn more from the director.

36
00:04:46,686 --> 00:04:47,453
Release the occluder.

37
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:56,863
Qiangwei.

38
00:04:58,231 --> 00:04:58,665
It's over.

39
00:05:02,869 --> 00:05:04,304
That was pretty fast.

40
00:05:06,773 --> 00:05:07,707
Another little red flower

41
00:05:08,374 --> 00:05:09,642
for our model patient.

42
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:24,957
Director, you wanted to see me?

43
00:05:28,227 --> 00:05:29,228
You've made great progress lately.

44
00:05:30,563 --> 00:05:32,165
Your clinical procedures in both

45
00:05:32,231 --> 00:05:33,333
Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery are getting much better.

46
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:34,567
The directors have all been praising you.

47
00:05:35,868 --> 00:05:37,603
And neither patients nor nurses

48
00:05:37,904 --> 00:05:39,238
have complained about you again.

49
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:41,374
Thank you, Director.

50
00:05:41,774 --> 00:05:42,709
I'll keep working hard.

51
00:05:43,943 --> 00:05:45,011
I don't want to let you down.

52
00:05:55,488 --> 00:05:56,255
Is this for me?

53
00:05:57,557 --> 00:05:58,491
No, no. This is too expensive.

54
00:05:58,591 --> 00:05:59,125
I can't accept it.

55
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:00,026
Take it.

56
00:06:00,493 --> 00:06:01,561
It's a tradition in our department.

57
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:05,965
In my first year of specialty training,

58
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:07,066
my teacher also gave me

59
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:07,800
a stethoscope.

60
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:11,370
I feel like I don't deserve it yet.

61
00:06:11,838 --> 00:06:12,638
Of course you do.

62
00:06:13,172 --> 00:06:13,673
You're my student.

63
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:14,507
How could you not deserve it?

64
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:16,109
Use it well.

65
00:06:16,743 --> 00:06:17,944
A stethoscope is a cardiologist's

66
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:18,945
closest companion.

67
00:06:19,912 --> 00:06:20,480
Thank you, Director.

68
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:25,718
How have you been lately?

69
00:06:26,853 --> 00:06:27,553
Are you holding up?

70
00:06:27,887 --> 00:06:29,055
Don't worry, Director.

71
00:06:29,422 --> 00:06:30,490
I'll take good care of myself.

72
00:06:31,424 --> 00:06:31,958
I won't let

73
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:33,393
what happened last time happen again.

74
00:06:34,827 --> 00:06:35,762
I know young people today

75
00:06:35,828 --> 00:06:37,163
dislike rat-race culture

76
00:06:37,530 --> 00:06:38,664
and don't buy into our old ways.

77
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:41,000
But there are no shortcuts

78
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:42,935
to becoming a good doctor.

79
00:06:43,669 --> 00:06:44,704
You have to study and practice hard.

80
00:06:45,171 --> 00:06:46,439
You're talented.

81
00:06:47,173 --> 00:06:48,107
You'll become

82
00:06:48,174 --> 00:06:49,108
an excellent doctor someday.

83
00:06:49,809 --> 00:06:50,877
That's why

84
00:06:50,877 --> 00:06:51,611
I expect a lot from you.

85
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,080
Sometimes

86
00:06:54,881 --> 00:06:55,848
that may put you under pressure.

87
00:06:56,949 --> 00:06:57,383
No.

88
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:01,287
Thank you for believing in me, Dr. Zhou.

89
00:07:02,889 --> 00:07:04,357
What you said

90
00:07:05,158 --> 00:07:05,892
means a lot to me.

91
00:07:07,326 --> 00:07:07,960
I admit,

92
00:07:08,494 --> 00:07:09,796
sometimes it is exhausting.

93
00:07:11,664 --> 00:07:12,765
But I enjoy

94
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:13,766
the process of improving.

95
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:16,969
I'll follow your example

96
00:07:18,371 --> 00:07:19,038
and keep aiming higher.

97
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:23,709
Thank you.

98
00:07:30,783 --> 00:07:31,851
It's beautiful.

99
00:07:31,984 --> 00:07:32,785
Director Zhou never disappoints.

100
00:07:32,885 --> 00:07:33,986
He went straight for the top model.

101
00:07:34,053 --> 00:07:35,388
This is so extravagant.

102
00:07:37,757 --> 00:07:38,491
Let me see it.

103
00:07:39,725 --> 00:07:40,526
Keep your distance.

104
00:07:42,361 --> 00:07:43,996
As if I'd break it just by touching it.

105
00:07:44,063 --> 00:07:45,198
So stingy.

106
00:07:45,598 --> 00:07:47,066
I can hardly bear to use it myself.

107
00:07:47,633 --> 00:07:48,668
I'll wait until I'm as capable

108
00:07:48,734 --> 00:07:49,569
as Director Zhou,

109
00:07:49,602 --> 00:07:50,303
then take it out

110
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:52,772
and use it until I retire.

111
00:07:52,905 --> 00:07:54,307
Fine. Make it a family heirloom.

112
00:07:54,407 --> 00:07:55,775
Pass it down to your students.

113
00:07:56,442 --> 00:07:56,843
Sis.

114
00:07:57,243 --> 00:07:58,277
Do you smell something?

115
00:08:01,247 --> 00:08:02,682
So sour.

116
00:08:05,885 --> 00:08:07,520
Jealous, envious, green with envy?

117
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,921
Go ask your Director Lin for one.

118
00:08:09,922 --> 00:08:11,390
I've noticed Cardiology

119
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:12,725
is really thriving lately.

120
00:08:19,599 --> 00:08:20,833
You're even working on gene editing.

121
00:08:23,603 --> 00:08:24,270
It's for the children.

122
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:26,105
Right.

123
00:08:27,273 --> 00:08:28,841
Weren't we short-handed before?

124
00:08:29,108 --> 00:08:30,409
Now Director Zhou

125
00:08:30,476 --> 00:08:31,711
and I are on the same page.

126
00:08:31,878 --> 00:08:32,678
So...

127
00:08:34,247 --> 00:08:34,714
Zhou Xiaofeng.

128
00:08:36,782 --> 00:08:38,117
Ouyang, don't put too much hope

129
00:08:38,317 --> 00:08:39,185
in Zhou Xiaofeng.

130
00:08:40,553 --> 00:08:42,788
As for Dongli Cardiology,

131
00:08:43,089 --> 00:08:44,190
just sell whatever you can

132
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:46,092
and make whatever you can.

133
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:46,826
Boss,

134
00:08:46,826 --> 00:08:47,927
what do you mean?

135
00:08:49,762 --> 00:08:50,796
It's too late.

136
00:08:51,764 --> 00:08:52,598
Let me put it this way:

137
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:54,433
even if Zhou Xiaofeng

138
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:55,668
blows the first-quarter numbers

139
00:08:55,801 --> 00:08:57,203
he blows the first-quarter numbers
through the roof,

140
00:08:57,503 --> 00:08:58,905
he still can't reverse the situation.

141
00:08:59,805 --> 00:09:00,873
Once Sheng Nian takes over,

142
00:09:02,174 --> 00:09:03,409
I doubt Zhou Xiaofeng

143
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:04,844
will even retain

144
00:09:04,844 --> 00:09:05,544
the authority to sign orders.

145
00:09:08,814 --> 00:09:10,116
Why?

146
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:13,185
A lot of Dongli Hospital's leaders

147
00:09:13,319 --> 00:09:14,854
support Sheng Nian.

148
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:16,789
And Wang Zhifeng goes without saying.

149
00:09:17,423 --> 00:09:18,157
Originally,

150
00:09:18,424 --> 00:09:19,926
the Heart Center director

151
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:22,161
was only half a rank above a department director,

152
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:23,129
without much real authority.

153
00:09:23,796 --> 00:09:25,031
But Wang Zhifeng,

154
00:09:25,364 --> 00:09:26,732
I heard, has delegated power.

155
00:09:27,533 --> 00:09:29,235
He gave the Heart Center director

156
00:09:29,335 --> 00:09:31,170
control over personnel and finances.

157
00:09:32,238 --> 00:09:32,838
Think about it.

158
00:09:33,639 --> 00:09:34,173
Power

159
00:09:34,507 --> 00:09:36,108
ultimately comes down to people and money.

160
00:09:36,842 --> 00:09:38,277
With those two swords of authority

161
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:39,078
in his hands,

162
00:09:39,545 --> 00:09:40,646
Sheng Nian

163
00:09:40,947 --> 00:09:41,814
will keep Zhou Xiaofeng

164
00:09:41,814 --> 00:09:42,848
firmly under his thumb.

165
00:09:43,382 --> 00:09:44,483
There'll be no chance to recover.

166
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:52,892
So because we can't show short-term results,

167
00:09:53,025 --> 00:09:54,327
President Wang won't support us?

168
00:09:58,397 --> 00:09:59,632
I was too optimistic before.

169
00:10:00,132 --> 00:10:01,434
I thought Professor Wu's endorsement

170
00:10:02,068 --> 00:10:03,469
would make the grant application easier.

171
00:10:04,203 --> 00:10:05,271
Professor Wu already laid

172
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:06,706
an excellent foundation

173
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:08,240
and is willing to keep

174
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,508
guiding and supporting us.

175
00:10:11,744 --> 00:10:15,147
Then why won't

176
00:10:15,715 --> 00:10:16,849
the team's second-in-command take over?

177
00:10:17,883 --> 00:10:19,385
By rights, they should

178
00:10:19,685 --> 00:10:21,087
understand the actual situation best.

179
00:10:21,854 --> 00:10:23,022
Could it be

180
00:10:23,856 --> 00:10:25,558
that they don't see much hope in the research?

181
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:26,993
It's okay.

182
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:28,794
If it's worth doing,

183
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:29,996
there'll be a way.

184
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:32,832
Didn't Ouyang say

185
00:10:33,432 --> 00:10:35,001
she's contacting sponsors?

186
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:40,239
If that doesn't work,

187
00:10:41,407 --> 00:10:42,975
I'll ask Director Ji

188
00:10:43,109 --> 00:10:43,809
and see

189
00:10:44,143 --> 00:10:45,678
whether she has any resources.

190
00:10:46,078 --> 00:10:47,146
Director Ji from Critical Care?

191
00:10:47,847 --> 00:10:48,280
Yes.

192
00:10:48,914 --> 00:10:49,915
I've been communicating with her

193
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:50,883
quite a lot lately.

194
00:10:51,283 --> 00:10:52,952
I also signed up

195
00:10:53,052 --> 00:10:53,786
for her new training program.

196
00:10:54,086 --> 00:10:54,954
She even asked

197
00:10:55,654 --> 00:10:56,756
whether I'd consider

198
00:10:56,789 --> 00:10:57,990
transferring to Critical Care.

199
00:11:01,694 --> 00:11:02,328
What do you mean?

200
00:11:03,829 --> 00:11:05,431
I am a little tempted.

201
00:11:06,132 --> 00:11:06,766
Maybe

202
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,734
that's my next move.

203
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:12,171
That works too.

204
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:13,839
Since you've signed up,

205
00:11:13,906 --> 00:11:14,874
go experience it first.

206
00:11:19,412 --> 00:11:19,812
By the way,

207
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,848
I visited Qiangwei before coming.

208
00:11:23,549 --> 00:11:24,550
Her procedure

209
00:11:24,550 --> 00:11:25,718
went very smoothly.

210
00:11:26,318 --> 00:11:27,787
A one-stop procedure suits her very well.

211
00:11:29,588 --> 00:11:30,556
I've also noticed

212
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:33,025
there are quite a few patients like her

213
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:34,527
who meet the indications

214
00:11:34,560 --> 00:11:35,928
and need one-stop treatment.

215
00:11:36,662 --> 00:11:38,731
I heard Fushan Hospital

216
00:11:38,964 --> 00:11:40,633
does one or two thousand cases a year.

217
00:11:40,766 --> 00:11:41,067
Yes.

218
00:11:45,404 --> 00:11:46,305
Then why hasn't our hospital

219
00:11:46,439 --> 00:11:47,673
started doing them?

220
00:11:50,476 --> 00:11:51,310
If hybrid surgery

221
00:11:51,343 --> 00:11:52,478
is collaboration across departments,

222
00:11:53,312 --> 00:11:54,213
then a one-stop procedure

223
00:11:54,246 --> 00:11:55,247
is collaboration across teams

224
00:11:55,481 --> 00:11:56,515
within one department.

225
00:11:57,216 --> 00:11:58,717
There are still practical limitations.

226
00:11:59,685 --> 00:12:00,886
That was before.

227
00:12:01,253 --> 00:12:02,388
When you had to ask another team,

228
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,155
it was troublesome.

229
00:12:03,489 --> 00:12:05,357
Now if you want to reassign internal staff,

230
00:12:05,758 --> 00:12:07,093
it's just one instruction away.

231
00:12:10,496 --> 00:12:10,930
True.

232
00:12:12,998 --> 00:12:13,566
Perhaps

233
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,935
that's my next move.

234
00:12:40,993 --> 00:12:41,627
Director Lin.

235
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:42,795
Didn't you run away?

236
00:12:42,795 --> 00:12:43,562
Why did you come back?

237
00:12:46,132 --> 00:12:46,432
I...

238
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:48,634
I didn't.

239
00:12:56,642 --> 00:12:57,309
Yiyi

240
00:12:58,244 --> 00:12:59,011
was worried I'd carry the pressure

241
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:00,012
of her illness,

242
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:01,680
and pressure from my family too,

243
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:03,349
so she broke up with me.

244
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:06,919
My head was a mess then,

245
00:13:07,353 --> 00:13:08,454
and I somehow agreed.

246
00:13:08,854 --> 00:13:09,989
But I regretted it the moment I walked out.

247
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:13,225
Then I thought,

248
00:13:14,393 --> 00:13:15,561
since my family objected,

249
00:13:16,562 --> 00:13:17,429
I should go home first

250
00:13:18,030 --> 00:13:19,231
and resolve things with them.

251
00:13:20,766 --> 00:13:21,734
So is it settled now?

252
00:13:24,036 --> 00:13:24,904
That's why I'm back.

253
00:13:25,871 --> 00:13:26,806
Then why are you still sitting there?

254
00:13:30,109 --> 00:13:30,676
Director Lin,

255
00:13:31,877 --> 00:13:32,344
I...

256
00:13:34,613 --> 00:13:36,649
I'm just not sure

257
00:13:36,849 --> 00:13:38,150
whether Yiyi will take me back.

258
00:13:38,851 --> 00:13:39,485
She may look

259
00:13:39,552 --> 00:13:40,486
like a cheerful little sun,

260
00:13:40,686 --> 00:13:41,954
lively, warm, and considerate,

261
00:13:42,454 --> 00:13:43,322
but she knows exactly what she wants.

262
00:13:43,722 --> 00:13:44,290
Once she decides, she doesn't change.

263
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:47,626
She said we were done, and I agreed.

264
00:13:49,295 --> 00:13:49,762
Besides,

265
00:13:50,429 --> 00:13:51,764
the problems between us

266
00:13:51,797 --> 00:13:52,598
aren't just about the two of us.

267
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:53,532
Do you still love her?

268
00:13:56,035 --> 00:13:56,735
That's what matters.

269
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:02,007
Yes.

270
00:14:02,908 --> 00:14:03,475
Does she love you?

271
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:05,744
She...

272
00:14:07,713 --> 00:14:08,280
She does.

273
00:14:09,048 --> 00:14:09,615
How do you know?

274
00:14:12,785 --> 00:14:13,652
The day we broke up,

275
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:15,955
she said a lot.

276
00:14:17,089 --> 00:14:18,524
I don't think she ever said she didn't love me.

277
00:14:22,294 --> 00:14:23,796
Then it's simple.

278
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:25,731
You love her, and she loves you.

279
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:26,932
Just tell her directly

280
00:14:26,966 --> 00:14:27,433
what you want to say.

281
00:14:28,634 --> 00:14:29,869
What if she rejects me?

282
00:14:30,669 --> 00:14:31,870
Then say it again.

283
00:14:31,971 --> 00:14:32,872
If once isn't enough, say it twice.

284
00:14:32,872 --> 00:14:33,839
If twice isn't enough, say it three times.

285
00:14:33,906 --> 00:14:35,007
Keep saying it

286
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:35,441
until she accepts you.

287
00:14:37,076 --> 00:14:38,143
It's that simple.

288
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:45,751
Is it really that simple?

289
00:14:48,487 --> 00:14:49,054
Director Lin,

290
00:14:49,755 --> 00:14:50,522
could you do it?

291
00:14:51,323 --> 00:14:51,690
I...

292
00:15:16,248 --> 00:15:16,615
Let's go.

293
00:15:18,117 --> 00:15:18,784
I don't blame you.

294
00:15:19,852 --> 00:15:20,119
Brother.

295
00:15:20,953 --> 00:15:21,587
I'm not leaving.

296
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:24,423
Tangtang.

297
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:26,558
Auntie.

298
00:15:27,393 --> 00:15:29,228
Yiyi's condition can't handle stress.

299
00:15:32,164 --> 00:15:32,665
Uncle.

300
00:15:33,732 --> 00:15:34,166
Auntie.

301
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,068
I'm sorry.

302
00:15:37,036 --> 00:15:37,703
Before,

303
00:15:38,304 --> 00:15:39,805
my family opposed us.

304
00:15:40,272 --> 00:15:40,806
My grandmother

305
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:42,975
was even hospitalized

306
00:15:43,042 --> 00:15:43,642
after getting too upset.

307
00:15:44,243 --> 00:15:45,110
I had to go back and care for her,

308
00:15:47,212 --> 00:15:48,514
so I didn't answer your calls.

309
00:15:51,850 --> 00:15:52,384
Tangtang,

310
00:15:54,653 --> 00:15:55,487
we understand.

311
00:15:57,189 --> 00:15:59,158
Yiyi's illness is lifelong.

312
00:15:59,725 --> 00:16:00,526
Any elder

313
00:16:01,393 --> 00:16:02,328
would struggle to accept it.

314
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,029
But now they've all agreed.

315
00:16:05,264 --> 00:16:06,198
I told them

316
00:16:06,765 --> 00:16:07,399
I love Yiyi

317
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:09,001
and will never

318
00:16:09,034 --> 00:16:09,601
leave her in this life.

319
00:16:11,503 --> 00:16:12,471
Once my family understood

320
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:13,305
how serious I was,

321
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:15,040
they stopped objecting.

322
00:16:15,874 --> 00:16:16,642
They even told me

323
00:16:17,609 --> 00:16:18,610
that since I'd made my choice,

324
00:16:19,244 --> 00:16:20,412
I had to treat Yiyi well

325
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:22,281
and never hurt her again.

326
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:23,682
Really.

327
00:16:24,516 --> 00:16:24,850
Brother.

328
00:16:25,751 --> 00:16:26,151
Auntie.

329
00:16:26,952 --> 00:16:27,486
Uncle.

330
00:16:28,053 --> 00:16:28,854
Please believe me.

331
00:16:39,231 --> 00:16:40,399
When I came back this time,

332
00:16:40,866 --> 00:16:42,267
my mom even gave me the household register.

333
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:47,106
Although

334
00:16:47,773 --> 00:16:48,507
I don't think

335
00:16:48,574 --> 00:16:49,308
we need it to get married anymore.

336
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:53,078
Brother,

337
00:16:53,946 --> 00:16:54,680
please help me.

338
00:16:55,914 --> 00:16:56,615
I'm not sure

339
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:57,616
whether Yiyi will take me back.

340
00:16:58,951 --> 00:16:59,318
Brother.

341
00:17:19,471 --> 00:17:20,839
Come on, everyone. Help yourselves.

342
00:17:21,039 --> 00:17:22,808
There are vegetables, seafood, and meat.

343
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:23,208
Everything.

344
00:17:23,409 --> 00:17:24,176
Can you reach it?

345
00:17:24,743 --> 00:17:25,677
Happy birthday.

346
00:17:25,844 --> 00:17:26,045
Thank you.

347
00:17:26,045 --> 00:17:26,645
Dr. Fang. Dr. Fang.

348
00:17:26,645 --> 00:17:27,479
Dr. Xiaoran, you're here.

349
00:17:27,613 --> 00:17:27,946
Sit here.

350
00:17:27,946 --> 00:17:28,647
We were just waiting for you.

351
00:17:30,449 --> 00:17:31,049
Hurry and eat something.

352
00:17:33,285 --> 00:17:33,852
Dr. Fang,

353
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:35,387
try my secret dipping sauce.

354
00:17:36,488 --> 00:17:36,922
Thank you.

355
00:17:37,689 --> 00:17:38,223
So thoughtful.

356
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:39,024
He's really showing off.

357
00:17:40,926 --> 00:17:41,493
I heard

358
00:17:42,394 --> 00:17:43,495
the girl with the cardiac trauma—

359
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:44,596
her boyfriend

360
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:46,398
disappeared for a few days, then came back.

361
00:17:47,232 --> 00:17:48,367
I saw him visiting.

362
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,001
He was already there.

363
00:17:50,836 --> 00:17:51,870
The two of them started talking

364
00:17:52,504 --> 00:17:53,505
and soon were laughing together.

365
00:17:54,373 --> 00:17:55,074
Yan Yiyi

366
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:56,375
is recovering better and better.

367
00:17:56,442 --> 00:17:57,543
She hasn't had

368
00:17:57,643 --> 00:17:58,477
another fainting spell.

369
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:00,813
That's the power of love.

370
00:18:01,346 --> 00:18:03,215
Pure-hearted romantics like him

371
00:18:03,515 --> 00:18:04,116
are rare these days.

372
00:18:04,316 --> 00:18:05,084
Exactly.

373
00:18:05,684 --> 00:18:06,385
That young man is solid.

374
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:07,319
He's young,

375
00:18:07,486 --> 00:18:08,987
but dependable and responsible.

376
00:18:09,488 --> 00:18:10,522
Imagine if, over some issue,

377
00:18:10,656 --> 00:18:11,423
he really lost

378
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:12,791
the girl he loved.

379
00:18:12,791 --> 00:18:13,725
He'd regret it

380
00:18:14,293 --> 00:18:15,394
for the rest of his life.

381
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:17,129
There'd be nowhere to cry.

382
00:18:17,229 --> 00:18:17,830
Exactly.

383
00:18:18,464 --> 00:18:18,864
Right?

384
00:18:20,332 --> 00:18:20,632
Yes.

385
00:18:21,533 --> 00:18:22,468
Then let's use this chance

386
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:23,469
to wish Sister Beibei

387
00:18:23,669 --> 00:18:25,237
a happy birthday and a wonderful love life.

388
00:18:25,571 --> 00:18:25,904
All right?

389
00:18:25,904 --> 00:18:26,605
Thank you. Thank you, everyone.

390
00:18:26,638 --> 00:18:27,372
Thank you all.

391
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:28,407
Happy birthday.

392
00:18:29,074 --> 00:18:29,975
Forever eighteen.

393
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:31,743
Come on.

394
00:18:32,744 --> 00:18:33,912
All right, cut the cake.

395
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:42,187
You don't have to come every day.

396
00:18:43,322 --> 00:18:43,989
I want to.

397
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:45,524
If I can't see you

398
00:18:45,591 --> 00:18:46,391
with my own eyes every day,

399
00:18:46,725 --> 00:18:47,526
I won't feel at ease.

400
00:18:50,195 --> 00:18:50,896
I just

401
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:52,531
don't want you to get tired.

402
00:18:56,535 --> 00:18:56,869
Yiyi.

403
00:18:59,171 --> 00:18:59,805
I'm slow.

404
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:01,707
When you said we should break up,

405
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,208
I somehow agreed.

406
00:19:03,675 --> 00:19:05,077
You're not allowed to say that again.

407
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:07,679
Whatever comes, good or bad,

408
00:19:08,247 --> 00:19:09,147
we'll face it together.

409
00:19:09,615 --> 00:19:09,948
Okay?

410
00:19:11,183 --> 00:19:11,550
Okay.

411
00:19:15,053 --> 00:19:15,320
Here.

412
00:19:18,557 --> 00:19:19,725
What are we eating today?

413
00:19:20,559 --> 00:19:21,827
Open it and see.

414
00:19:23,128 --> 00:19:24,062
My brother made it again?

415
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:25,430
Here.

416
00:19:25,864 --> 00:19:26,465
Careful, it's hot.

417
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:30,169
By the way,

418
00:19:31,303 --> 00:19:32,971
when my brother gave me this today,

419
00:19:33,238 --> 00:19:34,173
I saw him carrying

420
00:19:34,273 --> 00:19:35,240
two thermos flasks, one in each hand.

421
00:19:36,174 --> 00:19:37,342
He even opened them

422
00:19:37,409 --> 00:19:38,510
to check which one

423
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:40,679
didn't have shredded wood ear mushrooms.

424
00:19:41,046 --> 00:19:42,314
I wonder who

425
00:19:44,082 --> 00:19:44,683
What do you mean?

426
00:19:46,451 --> 00:19:48,787
Are you saying my brother has someone?

427
00:19:58,664 --> 00:20:00,065
Hello? Anyone here?

428
00:20:00,599 --> 00:20:01,033
Young man,

429
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:02,467
are you family?

430
00:20:03,335 --> 00:20:04,303
She's been hospitalized so long.

431
00:20:04,570 --> 00:20:05,437
Why are you only coming now?

432
00:20:06,004 --> 00:20:08,040
No, I... I'm...

433
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:11,710
Why are you here?

434
00:20:13,912 --> 00:20:14,479
I...

435
00:20:16,315 --> 00:20:17,783
I only just heard you had surgery.

436
00:20:19,318 --> 00:20:20,152
It was a minor procedure.

437
00:20:20,586 --> 00:20:21,753
I'll be fine in a couple of days.

438
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:27,359
I brought you something to eat.

439
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:28,126
Want some?

440
00:20:28,727 --> 00:20:29,228
What is it?

441
00:20:29,928 --> 00:20:30,929
West Lake beef soup.

442
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:32,998
You didn't cook it there again, did you?

443
00:20:33,031 --> 00:20:33,632
No, no.

444
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:35,000
I made it at home.

445
00:20:35,801 --> 00:20:36,235
All right.

446
00:20:36,668 --> 00:20:37,436
I happen to be hungry.

447
00:20:41,106 --> 00:20:41,974
This one

448
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:43,175
has shredded wood ear mushrooms.

449
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:44,343
Okay.

450
00:20:50,682 --> 00:20:51,049
Dr. Fang,

451
00:20:52,117 --> 00:20:53,051
I collected some materials

452
00:20:53,118 --> 00:20:54,252
on gene editing for cardiomyopathy.

453
00:20:54,319 --> 00:20:55,053
Take a look.

454
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:55,454
Take a look.

455
00:20:55,854 --> 00:20:56,955
Maybe they'll be useful.

456
00:20:57,723 --> 00:20:58,690
This much?

457
00:21:00,359 --> 00:21:01,827
You must've spent a lot of time.

458
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:02,728
Not really.

459
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:03,929
We still thought it wasn't enough.

460
00:21:04,329 --> 00:21:04,997
We?

461
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:06,131
Who else?

462
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:08,166
Xiaoye.

463
00:21:09,201 --> 00:21:09,601
Artificial intelligence.

464
00:21:09,968 --> 00:21:10,836
I did it with AI.

465
00:21:10,869 --> 00:21:11,169
Artificial intelligence?

466
00:21:11,236 --> 00:21:12,371
AI is very useful now.

467
00:21:14,673 --> 00:21:16,041
Gene editing.

468
00:21:18,644 --> 00:21:19,011
Director,

469
00:21:19,311 --> 00:21:20,212
are you researching this?

470
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,015
Never mind what I'm researching.

471
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:23,782
Just look it up for me.

472
00:21:25,317 --> 00:21:26,251
Isn't that easy?

473
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:27,886
You can't even do this?

474
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:29,588
Of course I can.

475
00:21:29,721 --> 00:21:30,589
I was testing you.

476
00:21:35,560 --> 00:21:35,794
Done.

477
00:21:36,828 --> 00:21:37,362
There.

478
00:21:37,696 --> 00:21:37,929
Right.

479
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:40,332
But you have to verify the information.

480
00:21:40,599 --> 00:21:41,533
AI sometimes

481
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:42,868
fabricates sources.

482
00:21:43,335 --> 00:21:43,835
Dr. Fang,

483
00:21:44,069 --> 00:21:44,803
my AI

484
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:45,637
would never do that.

485
00:21:46,171 --> 00:21:47,673
You could say it's extremely

486
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:48,106
quick

487
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:49,174
and extremely

488
00:21:49,441 --> 00:21:50,208
resourceful.

489
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:52,344
Thank you for thinking of me.

490
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:53,545
Dr. Fang,

491
00:21:53,745 --> 00:21:54,746
if there's anything else

492
00:21:54,746 --> 00:21:55,847
you want to research,

493
00:21:55,881 --> 00:21:56,548
just tell me anytime.

494
00:21:56,748 --> 00:21:57,916
Leave it to me and AI.

495
00:21:58,317 --> 00:21:58,583
All right.

496
00:21:58,850 --> 00:21:59,317
Thanks.

497
00:21:59,584 --> 00:21:59,951
You're welcome.

498
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:01,386
I'll get going, Dr. Fang.

499
00:22:02,087 --> 00:22:02,554
Go ahead.

500
00:22:11,363 --> 00:22:11,797
All right.

501
00:22:12,197 --> 00:22:12,631
You gave it to her?

502
00:22:12,764 --> 00:22:13,131
I did.

503
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:13,865
How did she react?

504
00:22:14,366 --> 00:22:15,167
She was very happy

505
00:22:15,233 --> 00:22:16,335
and thought it was very useful.

506
00:22:20,072 --> 00:22:20,806
You didn't give yourself away?

507
00:22:24,242 --> 00:22:24,643
No.

508
00:22:28,513 --> 00:22:29,014
Almost.

509
00:22:29,081 --> 00:22:29,948
But I covered it up.

510
00:22:30,148 --> 00:22:31,650
I said I did it with AI.

511
00:22:34,086 --> 00:22:34,886
Who did you do it with?

512
00:22:35,287 --> 00:22:35,687
Artificial intelligence.

513
00:22:38,390 --> 00:22:39,191
Smart, right, Director?

514
00:22:42,361 --> 00:22:43,028
Stop following me.

515
00:22:44,229 --> 00:22:44,996
Just follow AI.

516
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:47,466
No, Director.

517
00:22:47,599 --> 00:22:48,934
Wasn't my idea smart?

518
00:22:53,638 --> 00:22:54,172
More.

519
00:22:54,906 --> 00:22:55,874
Walk around more.

520
00:22:56,308 --> 00:22:58,510
I ran into the doctor just now

521
00:22:58,543 --> 00:22:59,111
and asked.

522
00:22:59,444 --> 00:23:00,746
In your current condition,

523
00:23:00,946 --> 00:23:03,348
walking more

524
00:23:03,615 --> 00:23:04,583
will help your recovery.

525
00:23:05,083 --> 00:23:05,951
Got it.

526
00:23:06,885 --> 00:23:08,520
Actually, the incision on my leg

527
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:09,054
isn't very big.

528
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:10,889
It'll heal quickly.

529
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:13,525
How is Yiyi?

530
00:23:14,159 --> 00:23:15,327
Has she been transferred over?

531
00:23:16,628 --> 00:23:17,729
She was moved out early this morning.

532
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:19,464
Everything's settled.

533
00:23:19,598 --> 00:23:20,966
She's in the Cardiac Surgery ward across the hall.

534
00:23:22,801 --> 00:23:23,168
Brother.

535
00:23:25,370 --> 00:23:25,837
Yiyi.

536
00:23:29,808 --> 00:23:30,308
Dad. Mom.

537
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:33,311
Why are you here?

538
00:23:34,079 --> 00:23:34,846
Can't we come?

539
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:37,682
No.

540
00:23:39,284 --> 00:23:40,118
Hello, Uncle and Auntie.

541
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:40,685
Hello, Yiyi.

542
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:42,120
Hello, Qiangwei.

543
00:23:42,754 --> 00:23:43,522
Yiyi

544
00:23:43,522 --> 00:23:44,756
insisted on coming to see you.

545
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:45,624
Sorry to bother you.

546
00:23:46,391 --> 00:23:47,092
Not at all.

547
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,361
I finally get to meet you in person.

548
00:23:49,561 --> 00:23:50,128
Well,

549
00:23:50,595 --> 00:23:52,197
my brother used to mention you all the time.

550
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:56,168
You seem to be recovering well.

551
00:23:56,468 --> 00:23:57,235
You look good.

552
00:23:57,736 --> 00:23:58,303
Yes.

553
00:23:58,570 --> 00:23:59,871
I'll probably be discharged in a couple of days.

554
00:24:00,806 --> 00:24:01,640
That's good. That's good.

555
00:24:02,641 --> 00:24:03,074
Lao Yan.

556
00:24:03,308 --> 00:24:03,875
Come on.

557
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:04,442
Right.

558
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:06,444
We brought some daily necessities.

559
00:24:06,645 --> 00:24:08,513
We weren't sure whether you'd like them.

560
00:24:09,114 --> 00:24:10,148
This is too much.

561
00:24:10,582 --> 00:24:11,049
Not at all.

562
00:24:11,316 --> 00:24:12,484
Right, and this too.

563
00:24:14,085 --> 00:24:14,953
Yiyi

564
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,721
spent a long time choosing it for you.

565
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:18,557
She had me order it online.

566
00:24:19,891 --> 00:24:20,625
What is it?

567
00:24:20,759 --> 00:24:21,159
Give it to me.

568
00:24:33,238 --> 00:24:34,906
Sister Qiangwei, do you like peacocks?

569
00:24:44,783 --> 00:24:46,685
When my husband was alive,

570
00:24:47,118 --> 00:24:49,287
he was a zookeeper.

571
00:24:49,988 --> 00:24:50,956
He told me

572
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:53,491
animals kept in cages

573
00:24:53,925 --> 00:24:55,293
always lost their spirit.

574
00:24:56,127 --> 00:24:57,896
My child's textbook

575
00:24:58,163 --> 00:25:00,732
had a poem about peacocks flying southeast.

576
00:25:01,266 --> 00:25:02,000
My husband said

577
00:25:02,033 --> 00:25:03,468
he had never seen

578
00:25:03,735 --> 00:25:05,170
a peacock actually fly.

579
00:25:06,404 --> 00:25:07,472
So this time I thought,

580
00:25:07,906 --> 00:25:08,974
after my surgery

581
00:25:09,407 --> 00:25:10,041
and discharge,

582
00:25:10,609 --> 00:25:11,843
I must go to Yunnan

583
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:13,945
and see

584
00:25:14,446 --> 00:25:15,614
how wild peacocks fly.

585
00:25:23,922 --> 00:25:24,656
Qiangwei,

586
00:25:25,223 --> 00:25:26,091
promise me

587
00:25:26,424 --> 00:25:27,592
you'll get well.

588
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,427
We'll go together.

589
00:25:37,135 --> 00:25:38,203
The moment I saw this,

590
00:25:38,403 --> 00:25:39,004
I chose it.

591
00:25:39,771 --> 00:25:40,438
I don't know why,

592
00:25:40,972 --> 00:25:42,040
but I felt you'd like it.

593
00:25:43,508 --> 00:25:44,743
Thank you. I love it.

594
00:25:46,011 --> 00:25:46,611
That's good.

595
00:25:47,212 --> 00:25:47,479
Here.

596
00:25:47,812 --> 00:25:49,114
If you like it, let me put it on you.

597
00:25:57,255 --> 00:25:57,589
Auntie Yang.

598
00:25:58,390 --> 00:25:59,624
I don't have

599
00:26:01,026 --> 00:26:01,993
any family left in this world.

600
00:26:05,997 --> 00:26:07,265
Qiangwei,

601
00:26:08,133 --> 00:26:10,201
when the time comes, I'll find

602
00:26:10,602 --> 00:26:11,303
a job at a nail salon

603
00:26:12,470 --> 00:26:13,104
and support you.

604
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:17,442
Okay.

605
00:26:18,310 --> 00:26:19,077
Then

606
00:26:19,277 --> 00:26:20,412
I'll cook delicious food for you

607
00:26:21,012 --> 00:26:22,480
and take good care of you.

608
00:26:41,399 --> 00:26:42,267
Let's take a photo.

609
00:26:43,468 --> 00:26:44,102
So beautiful.

610
00:26:45,570 --> 00:26:46,071
Wonderful.

611
00:26:51,676 --> 00:26:52,644
I'm sorry, I...

612
00:26:57,849 --> 00:26:58,717
I'm sorry, I...

613
00:26:59,484 --> 00:27:00,185
Come here, Qiangwei.

614
00:27:15,734 --> 00:27:17,002
It's okay. It's okay.

615
00:27:27,212 --> 00:27:28,279
Our Chunjing

616
00:27:28,913 --> 00:27:30,315
has changed so much lately.

617
00:27:30,915 --> 00:27:31,916
Only later did I learn

618
00:27:32,117 --> 00:27:33,284
that you helped him.

619
00:27:35,153 --> 00:27:36,254
I truly want to thank you.

620
00:27:39,124 --> 00:27:41,593
We were just strangers

621
00:27:41,593 --> 00:27:43,228
who met in the hospital

622
00:27:44,729 --> 00:27:45,730
and helped each other.

623
00:27:56,241 --> 00:27:56,841
Well...

624
00:27:57,876 --> 00:27:58,343
Well...

625
00:27:59,411 --> 00:28:01,279
If you need any food or supplies,

626
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:02,113
just tell me.

627
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:03,348
We live right across the hall,

628
00:28:03,448 --> 00:28:03,948
so it's convenient.

629
00:28:04,149 --> 00:28:05,016
I'll have Chunjing

630
00:28:05,016 --> 00:28:05,550
bring them over.

631
00:28:05,950 --> 00:28:06,584
Thank you, Auntie.

632
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:10,088
I heard

633
00:28:10,722 --> 00:28:11,790
while I was asleep,

634
00:28:12,190 --> 00:28:13,792
you came over and secretly filmed me.

635
00:28:14,492 --> 00:28:15,193
So, Sister Qiangwei,

636
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:17,595
do I snore?

637
00:28:19,931 --> 00:28:21,833
She's lying to you. You're really loud.

638
00:28:34,712 --> 00:28:35,246
Brother.

639
00:28:36,114 --> 00:28:37,048
Why did Sister Qiangwei

640
00:28:37,048 --> 00:28:38,249
react so strongly

641
00:28:38,883 --> 00:28:39,884
when she saw the peacock shawl?

642
00:28:40,051 --> 00:28:40,785
I think

643
00:28:41,352 --> 00:28:42,921
there must be a story behind it.

644
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:45,790
The first time I met Qiangwei,

645
00:28:45,824 --> 00:28:47,192
I thought she was kind-hearted.

646
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:48,293
Son,

647
00:28:49,027 --> 00:28:50,929
she's had a hard life on her own.

648
00:28:50,929 --> 00:28:52,831
We should look out for her.

649
00:28:53,731 --> 00:28:54,265
Girls

650
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:56,000
should cry less and smile more.

651
00:28:56,868 --> 00:28:58,436
Brother, you need to work harder.

652
00:28:58,903 --> 00:29:00,271
Nothing's even started yet.

653
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,207
Exactly. Stop interfering with him.

654
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:02,841
Focus on

655
00:29:02,874 --> 00:29:03,775
your own task first.

656
00:29:04,275 --> 00:29:04,709
Me?

657
00:29:05,343 --> 00:29:06,211
What task do I have?

658
00:29:06,845 --> 00:29:08,012
Rest and recover.

659
00:29:08,313 --> 00:29:08,947
Talk less and lie down more.

660
00:29:09,814 --> 00:29:10,682
Follow doctor's orders.

661
00:29:11,082 --> 00:29:11,850
No showing off.

662
00:29:12,851 --> 00:29:14,552
You two are really in sync.

663
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:20,391
By the way, Mom,

664
00:29:21,359 --> 00:29:22,927
has our genetic test report

665
00:29:22,994 --> 00:29:23,628
come back yet?

666
00:29:24,195 --> 00:29:25,997
I asked the doctor. It'll take a month.

667
00:29:27,632 --> 00:29:28,566
There's no rush.

668
00:29:29,067 --> 00:29:30,068
Right, no rush.

669
00:29:30,168 --> 00:29:31,035
Get some rest.

670
00:29:31,035 --> 00:29:31,402
Rest.

671
00:29:31,636 --> 00:29:32,070
Lie down.

672
00:29:42,013 --> 00:29:43,047
What are you two whispering about?

673
00:29:43,915 --> 00:29:44,516
A secret.

674
00:29:47,685 --> 00:29:48,253
West Lake beef soup.

675
00:29:49,521 --> 00:29:50,054
Thank you.

676
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:02,600
I'll take these downstairs first.

677
00:30:02,967 --> 00:30:03,334
Okay.

678
00:30:04,836 --> 00:30:05,303
Director Lin.

679
00:30:09,674 --> 00:30:10,074
Director Lin.

680
00:30:11,109 --> 00:30:12,677
Why is he helping you pack?

681
00:30:12,911 --> 00:30:14,012
Just a friend helping out.

682
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:17,115
I heard you're being discharged,

683
00:30:17,515 --> 00:30:18,349
so I came to see you.

684
00:30:18,716 --> 00:30:19,317
Thank you, Director Lin.

685
00:30:19,717 --> 00:30:20,518
Remember,

686
00:30:20,718 --> 00:30:21,586
after you go home, come for follow-ups on time.

687
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:22,687
You can contact me directly,

688
00:30:24,055 --> 00:30:25,023
or Director Zhou.

689
00:30:25,423 --> 00:30:25,757
Okay.

690
00:30:31,829 --> 00:30:32,130
Qiangwei.

691
00:30:32,130 --> 00:30:33,531
Director Xiaofeng. Dr. Xiaoran.

692
00:30:33,798 --> 00:30:34,365
You're being discharged?

693
00:30:34,632 --> 00:30:35,066
Yes.

694
00:30:36,267 --> 00:30:36,835
Remember,

695
00:30:37,202 --> 00:30:38,036
come back for follow-up.

696
00:30:38,169 --> 00:30:39,103
Come directly to me.

697
00:30:39,437 --> 00:30:39,971
If you can't find me,

698
00:30:40,038 --> 00:30:40,805
send me a message.

699
00:30:47,245 --> 00:30:47,545
Okay.

700
00:30:48,246 --> 00:30:48,646
Also,

701
00:30:49,247 --> 00:30:50,215
I've reviewed some cases

702
00:30:50,615 --> 00:30:51,950
and consulted Neurology experts.

703
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:53,117
There is still a chance

704
00:30:53,318 --> 00:30:54,152
your vision

705
00:30:54,185 --> 00:30:55,119
could recover.

706
00:30:56,487 --> 00:30:58,356
Actually, it isn't a big problem.

707
00:30:58,690 --> 00:31:00,191
There's just a dark corner on one side.

708
00:31:00,558 --> 00:31:02,026
It helps me ignore troubling things

709
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:03,595
and look only ahead.

710
00:31:10,168 --> 00:31:11,269
Can we take a photo together?

711
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:16,474
Of course.

712
00:31:16,908 --> 00:31:17,375
Okay.

713
00:31:19,410 --> 00:31:19,844
Director Lin.

714
00:31:24,082 --> 00:31:25,583
Three, two, one.

715
00:31:31,789 --> 00:31:32,891
The last time the three of you

716
00:31:32,924 --> 00:31:34,158
stood by my bed

717
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:36,294
was when you were persuading me to have surgery.

718
00:31:40,398 --> 00:31:41,432
You were even lying to me then.

719
00:31:43,835 --> 00:31:44,602
And Dr. Xiaoran,

720
00:31:44,869 --> 00:31:45,503
you were part of it too.

721
00:31:47,238 --> 00:31:48,439
I objected at the time.

722
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,575
You object to everything I do.

723
00:31:50,909 --> 00:31:51,643
So do you.

724
00:31:53,645 --> 00:31:55,013
Let me say one more thing.

725
00:31:55,747 --> 00:31:56,748
Watching you two lately

726
00:31:56,848 --> 00:31:57,715
here in the hospital,

727
00:31:57,782 --> 00:31:59,751
I've felt really uncomfortable.

728
00:32:01,152 --> 00:32:01,986
In my heart,

729
00:32:01,986 --> 00:32:03,321
you two are the best partners.

730
00:32:03,554 --> 00:32:04,789
Truly the best partners.

731
00:32:09,627 --> 00:32:11,062
If Auntie Yang were still here,

732
00:32:12,797 --> 00:32:13,765
she'd say the same.

733
00:32:23,007 --> 00:32:23,708
Congratulations on your discharge.

734
00:32:23,875 --> 00:32:25,109
I have surgery. I'll go first.

735
00:32:33,117 --> 00:32:34,452
I'm still bad with words.

736
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:40,224
Director Zhou. Dr. Fang.

737
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:41,225
You're here too.

738
00:32:42,527 --> 00:32:43,094
Everything packed?

739
00:32:43,227 --> 00:32:43,695
All done.

740
00:32:43,795 --> 00:32:44,629
Give it to me. I'll carry it.

741
00:32:45,730 --> 00:32:47,131
Director Xiaofeng. Dr. Xiaoran.

742
00:32:48,933 --> 00:32:49,434
Goodbye.

743
00:32:51,769 --> 00:32:52,670
Let's not meet at the hospital again.

744
00:32:53,071 --> 00:32:54,238
I'll visit your nail salon later.

745
00:32:54,872 --> 00:32:55,206
All right.

746
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:56,808
You'd better come.

747
00:33:07,051 --> 00:33:07,652
Factory Director Ma.

748
00:33:08,519 --> 00:33:09,053
What is this?

749
00:33:13,091 --> 00:33:13,725
Fat enough?

750
00:33:18,262 --> 00:33:19,163
When my aunt heard

751
00:33:19,197 --> 00:33:20,198
I was coming to your hospital,

752
00:33:20,531 --> 00:33:21,599
she had me choose

753
00:33:21,632 --> 00:33:23,334
the fattest lamb

754
00:33:23,334 --> 00:33:23,935
to bring you.

755
00:33:25,002 --> 00:33:25,570
And this.

756
00:33:26,204 --> 00:33:27,238
Hanxuan's mother

757
00:33:27,438 --> 00:33:29,007
specially asked me to bring it.

758
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:30,908
We grew it ourselves.

759
00:33:31,409 --> 00:33:33,077
No pesticides. Safe and healthy.

760
00:33:33,745 --> 00:33:34,846
Thank you, Director Ma.

761
00:33:35,079 --> 00:33:35,880
I appreciate it,

762
00:33:36,247 --> 00:33:37,715
but I rarely cook.

763
00:33:38,049 --> 00:33:39,384
Please take these back.

764
00:33:40,685 --> 00:33:42,153
They're already here.

765
00:33:42,253 --> 00:33:43,888
How could I take them back?

766
00:33:44,489 --> 00:33:46,090
You saved our lives.

767
00:33:47,959 --> 00:33:48,326
All right.

768
00:33:48,826 --> 00:33:50,094
I'll keep the vegetables.

769
00:33:50,528 --> 00:33:51,729
But please take the lamb back.

770
00:33:56,667 --> 00:33:57,068
How about this:

771
00:33:57,268 --> 00:33:58,202
I'll slaughter it at home,

772
00:33:58,269 --> 00:33:58,803
cut it into pieces,

773
00:33:59,003 --> 00:33:59,470
and bring it back to you.

774
00:33:59,470 --> 00:33:59,971
No, no.

775
00:34:00,171 --> 00:34:00,471
Director,

776
00:34:00,505 --> 00:34:01,472
how is your aunt recovering?

777
00:34:01,973 --> 00:34:02,707
Very well.

778
00:34:03,074 --> 00:34:04,008
Full of energy.

779
00:34:04,242 --> 00:34:04,709
That's wonderful.

780
00:34:05,443 --> 00:34:06,077
Have a seat.

781
00:34:06,878 --> 00:34:07,845
Okay, okay.

782
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:12,683
Sorry to trouble you

783
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:13,684
to make a special trip.

784
00:34:15,319 --> 00:34:15,787
Director,

785
00:34:16,354 --> 00:34:17,388
don't say that.

786
00:34:17,688 --> 00:34:18,289
You're the lifesaver

787
00:34:18,322 --> 00:34:19,757
of our whole village.

788
00:34:21,192 --> 00:34:21,926
I came

789
00:34:22,393 --> 00:34:24,662
partly to bring you these,

790
00:34:24,996 --> 00:34:26,330
but actually, I also came to see a doctor.

791
00:34:27,365 --> 00:34:28,466
I've had migraines

792
00:34:28,466 --> 00:34:29,567
for over ten years.

793
00:34:31,436 --> 00:34:32,703
I've been to our county hospital

794
00:34:32,804 --> 00:34:33,438
and township hospital,

795
00:34:33,604 --> 00:34:34,405
and they said

796
00:34:34,705 --> 00:34:35,506
there's nothing wrong

797
00:34:35,506 --> 00:34:36,441
with my brain.

798
00:34:36,874 --> 00:34:38,309
But medicine doesn't help.

799
00:34:39,343 --> 00:34:40,878
Have you ever had an echocardiogram?

800
00:34:41,245 --> 00:34:41,879
An echocardiogram?

801
00:34:43,014 --> 00:34:43,414
No.

802
00:34:43,614 --> 00:34:44,749
Wait, Director.

803
00:34:45,349 --> 00:34:46,584
Can migraines

804
00:34:46,717 --> 00:34:48,152
really be related to the heart?

805
00:34:49,287 --> 00:34:51,155
A patent foramen ovale.

806
00:34:51,322 --> 00:34:52,690
What kind of illness is that?

807
00:34:53,291 --> 00:34:54,892
In the fetal stage,

808
00:34:54,959 --> 00:34:55,927
there is a normal passage

809
00:34:55,993 --> 00:34:57,628
in the atrial septum

810
00:34:57,762 --> 00:34:58,496
called the foramen ovale.

811
00:34:58,596 --> 00:34:59,964
It's this green dot here.

812
00:35:00,598 --> 00:35:01,999
Usually, within two months after birth,

813
00:35:02,166 --> 00:35:03,067
it closes naturally.

814
00:35:03,201 --> 00:35:04,435
If it hasn't closed by age three,

815
00:35:04,435 --> 00:35:05,636
it's called a patent foramen ovale.

816
00:35:07,038 --> 00:35:07,705
Three years old?

817
00:35:09,507 --> 00:35:11,042
I'm already fifty-three.

818
00:35:11,909 --> 00:35:13,644
Since other causes have been ruled out,

819
00:35:13,811 --> 00:35:14,745
your migraines

820
00:35:14,946 --> 00:35:16,314
are probably related

821
00:35:16,314 --> 00:35:17,315
to the patent foramen ovale.

822
00:35:17,849 --> 00:35:18,983
The scans also show

823
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:20,151
multiple

824
00:35:20,151 --> 00:35:21,319
old cerebral infarcts.

825
00:35:21,719 --> 00:35:22,386
They were very likely

826
00:35:22,453 --> 00:35:23,754
caused by the PFO.

827
00:35:24,288 --> 00:35:25,189
And the numbness in your hand

828
00:35:25,523 --> 00:35:26,357
is most likely

829
00:35:26,357 --> 00:35:27,425
a residual effect of the strokes.

830
00:35:27,892 --> 00:35:28,893
I never imagined

831
00:35:28,926 --> 00:35:30,928
headaches could really be linked to the heart.

832
00:35:32,563 --> 00:35:33,397
Can it be treated?

833
00:35:34,532 --> 00:35:35,066
Yes.

834
00:35:36,767 --> 00:35:37,635
My goodness.

835
00:35:38,269 --> 00:35:39,570
I'm considering arranging

836
00:35:39,670 --> 00:35:40,471
a transcatheter closure procedure.

837
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:43,407
This...

838
00:35:44,108 --> 00:35:45,209
This is the occluder.

839
00:35:47,345 --> 00:35:49,046
So this is the occluder?

840
00:35:50,248 --> 00:35:51,449
We'll deliver this small device

841
00:35:51,716 --> 00:35:52,717
through a blood vessel in your leg

842
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:53,551
into the heart.

843
00:35:53,951 --> 00:35:54,986
It opens like a tiny umbrella

844
00:35:55,119 --> 00:35:55,686
and seals

845
00:35:56,087 --> 00:35:57,555
the hole we just discussed.

846
00:35:58,289 --> 00:35:59,991
Afterward, your risk of stroke

847
00:36:00,091 --> 00:36:00,758
will decrease.

848
00:36:01,526 --> 00:36:02,426
And your migraines

849
00:36:02,426 --> 00:36:03,394
will likely improve too.

850
00:36:04,095 --> 00:36:04,829
My goodness.

851
00:36:05,763 --> 00:36:07,064
If I'd known about

852
00:36:07,265 --> 00:36:07,865
this high-tech treatment,

853
00:36:08,232 --> 00:36:09,033
I wouldn't have suffered headaches

854
00:36:09,066 --> 00:36:10,268
for more than ten years.

855
00:36:15,573 --> 00:36:16,007
Director,

856
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:17,842
with Qiangwei's case as support,

857
00:36:18,109 --> 00:36:19,277
the application for a specialty clinic

858
00:36:19,343 --> 00:36:20,611
for one-stop AF treatment

859
00:36:20,678 --> 00:36:21,312
has been approved.

860
00:36:21,412 --> 00:36:22,413
It can open next week.

861
00:36:23,114 --> 00:36:24,081
Director Guo, Monday morning.

862
00:36:24,148 --> 00:36:24,916
You, Wednesday afternoon.

863
00:36:25,082 --> 00:36:25,449
Okay.

864
00:36:26,284 --> 00:36:27,351
Has publicity been arranged?

865
00:36:27,985 --> 00:36:28,653
Yes.

866
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,922
The hospital's publicity team contacted

867
00:36:30,988 --> 00:36:31,889
several traditional media outlets.

868
00:36:32,123 --> 00:36:32,390
Also,

869
00:36:32,623 --> 00:36:33,991
Qiangwei agreed to be interviewed.

870
00:36:34,158 --> 00:36:35,126
She's willing to cooperate.

871
00:36:35,493 --> 00:36:36,360
And there are several

872
00:36:36,427 --> 00:36:37,094
self-media channels

873
00:36:37,128 --> 00:36:38,229
previously contacted by Manager Ouyang.

874
00:36:38,529 --> 00:36:39,597
Their reach is quite strong.

875
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:43,134
Manager Ouyang is very helpful.

876
00:36:43,568 --> 00:36:44,769
Xiao Xuanfeng's numbers are so high

877
00:36:44,869 --> 00:36:45,403
because of her.

878
00:36:45,570 --> 00:36:46,771
Although the account was handed to me,

879
00:36:46,837 --> 00:36:48,039
she personally handled

880
00:36:48,072 --> 00:36:49,006
many of the coordination tasks.

881
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:50,174
So by the time things

882
00:36:50,174 --> 00:36:50,908
reach me,

883
00:36:51,008 --> 00:36:52,210
most arrangements are already in place.

884
00:36:55,313 --> 00:36:57,014
Director Zhou treated me very well.

885
00:36:57,815 --> 00:36:58,649
Director Zhou treated me very well.

886
00:36:58,883 --> 00:37:00,518
He cured this illness of mine.

887
00:37:00,952 --> 00:37:01,452
No problem.

888
00:37:02,753 --> 00:37:04,055
Please proceed to the specialty clinic.

889
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:05,222
Patient number fifteen, Lu Xinwang,

890
00:37:05,523 --> 00:37:06,724
please go to Consultation Room Ten.

891
00:37:06,991 --> 00:37:07,491
Old Lu.

892
00:37:08,125 --> 00:37:08,626
Yes, yes.

893
00:37:09,427 --> 00:37:09,927
Director Zhou.

894
00:37:10,828 --> 00:37:11,395
Factory Director Ma.

895
00:37:11,896 --> 00:37:12,463
I'm back again.

896
00:37:12,863 --> 00:37:13,364
How are you?

897
00:37:13,798 --> 00:37:14,398
I'm doing great.

898
00:37:14,799 --> 00:37:16,200
I brought my neighbor.

899
00:37:16,334 --> 00:37:18,336
He also wants you

900
00:37:19,036 --> 00:37:20,271
And who are these people?

901
00:37:21,005 --> 00:37:21,906
They're all from our village.

902
00:37:22,406 --> 00:37:23,908
They were seen

903
00:37:24,008 --> 00:37:24,842
at other hospitals first

904
00:37:25,042 --> 00:37:25,876
and diagnosed with atrial fibrillation.

905
00:37:26,477 --> 00:37:27,712
So I brought everyone

906
00:37:27,945 --> 00:37:28,813
to see you together.

907
00:37:28,846 --> 00:37:29,480
Please take a look.

908
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:31,716
Which one is Lu Xinwang?

909
00:37:32,149 --> 00:37:32,650
Here.

910
00:37:32,650 --> 00:37:33,084
Me, me.

911
00:37:34,085 --> 00:37:36,487
Then numbers sixteen, seventeen, and eighteen

912
00:37:36,754 --> 00:37:38,155
are all ours too.

913
00:37:38,522 --> 00:37:39,123
I'm also

914
00:37:39,624 --> 00:37:40,691
here for a follow-up.

915
00:37:41,325 --> 00:37:42,526
Let's do this one at a time.

916
00:37:42,927 --> 00:37:44,295
Please wait outside for now.

917
00:37:45,363 --> 00:37:46,631
Okay, okay. Let's go out first.

918
00:37:46,797 --> 00:37:47,632
These are ours.

919
00:37:47,732 --> 00:37:48,065
All right.

920
00:37:48,466 --> 00:37:49,600
There are rules here.

921
00:37:58,042 --> 00:37:58,909
The growth potential

922
00:37:58,943 --> 00:37:59,677
for valve procedures

923
00:37:59,844 --> 00:38:00,811
is already very limited.

924
00:38:01,412 --> 00:38:02,413
One-stop treatment

925
00:38:02,446 --> 00:38:03,714
is the real blue ocean.

926
00:38:04,348 --> 00:38:05,149
Morale in the department

927
00:38:05,149 --> 00:38:06,317
has risen sharply lately.

928
00:38:06,584 --> 00:38:07,985
We should've done this long ago.

929
00:38:09,353 --> 00:38:09,854
And

930
00:38:10,321 --> 00:38:11,522
I attended a meeting yesterday.

931
00:38:12,023 --> 00:38:13,124
Afterward,

932
00:38:13,324 --> 00:38:13,958
many colleagues

933
00:38:14,025 --> 00:38:15,926
came to talk to me about one-stop treatment.

934
00:38:16,727 --> 00:38:17,728
I think the outside world

935
00:38:17,795 --> 00:38:19,230
is paying a lot of attention to us now.

936
00:38:19,597 --> 00:38:20,264
That shows

937
00:38:20,364 --> 00:38:21,732
Dongli Cardiology's reputation

938
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:22,600
across Dongjiang

939
00:38:22,733 --> 00:38:24,035
is growing stronger.

940
00:38:29,974 --> 00:38:30,408
Head Nurse.

941
00:38:31,409 --> 00:38:31,876
Director Zhou.

942
00:38:32,410 --> 00:38:33,644
We've had a lot of patients these past two days,

943
00:38:33,711 --> 00:38:34,445
especially those

944
00:38:34,512 --> 00:38:35,279
waiting for one-stop treatment.

945
00:38:35,513 --> 00:38:36,847
Quite a few are still waiting for admission.

946
00:38:37,014 --> 00:38:38,082
So for bed turnover,

947
00:38:38,282 --> 00:38:39,250
we may need

948
00:38:39,250 --> 00:38:39,750
your extra help.

949
00:38:40,284 --> 00:38:40,751
No problem.

950
00:38:41,852 --> 00:38:42,253
Director Zhou,

951
00:38:42,853 --> 00:38:44,455
there's something I wanted to ask.

952
00:38:45,189 --> 00:38:46,190
Give me those two charts

953
00:38:46,190 --> 00:38:46,757
from just now.

954
00:38:47,825 --> 00:38:48,826
These two inpatients,

955
00:38:49,427 --> 00:38:50,094
Lu Xinwang

956
00:38:51,162 --> 00:38:51,762
and Shen Shuxian,

957
00:38:52,797 --> 00:38:53,464
also need

958
00:38:53,531 --> 00:38:54,465
one-stop treatment?

959
00:38:55,466 --> 00:38:56,534
I saw both of them

960
00:38:57,134 --> 00:38:57,835
were transferred by you

961
00:38:57,835 --> 00:38:58,803
to Director Guo.

962
00:39:04,075 --> 00:39:05,443
They appear to meet the indications.

963
00:39:05,943 --> 00:39:06,644
Is there a problem?

964
00:39:10,114 --> 00:39:10,915
As long as you've confirmed it.

965
00:39:12,383 --> 00:39:13,250
I'll make the arrangements.

966
00:39:13,984 --> 00:39:14,719
Thank you, Head Nurse.

967
00:39:14,885 --> 00:39:15,186
You're welcome.

968
00:39:15,553 --> 00:39:15,920
Thank you.

969
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:28,232
Director, you wanted to see me?

970
00:39:29,333 --> 00:39:29,867
I wanted to ask about

971
00:39:30,034 --> 00:39:30,735
those two patients,

972
00:39:31,335 --> 00:39:32,570
Shen Shuxian and Lu Xinwang.

973
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:34,271
I saw you're planning

974
00:39:34,371 --> 00:39:35,639
one-stop AF procedures for them.

975
00:39:35,639 --> 00:39:35,973
Yes.

976
00:39:36,507 --> 00:39:37,775
They fully meet

977
00:39:37,808 --> 00:39:38,476
the surgical criteria.

978
00:39:40,344 --> 00:39:41,545
I was just about to thank you

979
00:39:42,079 --> 00:39:43,080
for referring

980
00:39:43,114 --> 00:39:43,547
your patients to me.

981
00:39:44,815 --> 00:39:45,950
There's no yours or mine.

982
00:39:46,183 --> 00:39:46,951
They're the department's patients.

983
00:39:48,119 --> 00:39:48,519
It's just that

984
00:39:49,253 --> 00:39:50,354
I reviewed their records.

985
00:39:50,921 --> 00:39:52,089
Their conditions can also

986
00:39:52,156 --> 00:39:52,957
be managed with anticoagulants.

987
00:39:53,424 --> 00:39:54,625
What exactly did you tell them?

988
00:39:57,027 --> 00:39:57,561
Doctor,

989
00:39:58,896 --> 00:40:00,030
is my condition serious?

990
00:40:00,798 --> 00:40:01,999
It's relatively stable now.

991
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,367
But later,

992
00:40:03,567 --> 00:40:05,002
you'll still need

993
00:40:05,069 --> 00:40:06,604
long-term anticoagulant therapy,

994
00:40:07,671 --> 00:40:08,639
or you could have a minor procedure.

995
00:40:09,907 --> 00:40:10,875
A procedure is possible?

996
00:40:11,475 --> 00:40:11,842
Of course.

997
00:40:12,276 --> 00:40:13,744
It's a minor operation under local anesthesia.

998
00:40:14,078 --> 00:40:15,079
If recovery goes well,

999
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:16,113
you can be discharged in two days.

1000
00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:17,915
Given

1001
00:40:17,948 --> 00:40:19,316
your current condition,

1002
00:40:19,383 --> 00:40:20,684
if you take medication,

1003
00:40:20,885 --> 00:40:21,986
there is a certain risk

1004
00:40:22,052 --> 00:40:22,887
of cerebral hemorrhage.

1005
00:40:23,754 --> 00:40:24,388
Didn't your father

1006
00:40:24,588 --> 00:40:25,890
die of a brain hemorrhage?

1007
00:40:26,290 --> 00:40:27,358
We often see

1008
00:40:27,425 --> 00:40:28,492
elderly patients like this.

1009
00:40:28,626 --> 00:40:30,694
Too little medicine leads to thrombosis.

1010
00:40:30,995 --> 00:40:32,596
Too much leads to cerebral hemorrhage.

1011
00:40:33,197 --> 00:40:34,432
Paralysis, a vegetative state—

1012
00:40:34,532 --> 00:40:35,833
and ultimately delayed treatment.

1013
00:40:36,066 --> 00:40:36,834
It's a real shame.

1014
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,371
This condition is that serious?

1015
00:40:41,038 --> 00:40:43,207
So after this procedure,

1016
00:40:43,507 --> 00:40:44,809
I won't have another clot

1017
00:40:44,842 --> 00:40:46,210
and won't need lifelong medication?

1018
00:40:46,243 --> 00:40:46,510
Right?

1019
00:40:47,011 --> 00:40:49,213
The outcome is no worse than anticoagulants.

1020
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:51,048
And it reduces

1021
00:40:51,148 --> 00:40:53,083
the bleeding risk caused by medication.

1022
00:40:53,651 --> 00:40:55,085
I only added

1023
00:40:55,152 --> 00:40:56,987
that medication also carries risks.

1024
00:40:57,188 --> 00:40:58,556
Then they insisted on surgery.

1025
00:40:59,323 --> 00:41:01,158
The procedure is no less effective than medicine.

1026
00:41:01,759 --> 00:41:02,927
So I figured

1027
00:41:03,494 --> 00:41:04,495
the patients would think,

1028
00:41:04,562 --> 00:41:05,329
"Since I'm already here,

1029
00:41:05,496 --> 00:41:07,031
I'll spend the money and settle it once and for all,

1030
00:41:07,198 --> 00:41:07,865
for peace of mind."

1031
00:41:10,401 --> 00:41:10,801
Yes.

1032
00:41:11,502 --> 00:41:13,103
The patient's wishes should be considered,

1033
00:41:13,671 --> 00:41:14,605
but that doesn't mean—

1034
00:41:15,172 --> 00:41:15,506
Director,

1035
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:17,107
believe it or not,

1036
00:41:18,676 --> 00:41:19,743
if these two patients

1037
00:41:19,944 --> 00:41:20,845
leave Dongli today,

1038
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:23,214
they'll go to another hospital tomorrow

1039
00:41:23,247 --> 00:41:24,248
and have the procedure there.

1040
00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:26,584
Everything I'm doing

1041
00:41:26,650 --> 00:41:27,518
is for the good of our department.

1042
00:41:28,085 --> 00:41:29,253
And at the meeting you said

1043
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,455
that in the Heart Center director election,

1044
00:41:31,922 --> 00:41:32,823
you'd fight with your back to the wall.

1045
00:41:33,624 --> 00:41:34,892
I'm doing all this for you.

1046
00:41:52,910 --> 00:41:53,744
Hello, Amin.

1047
00:41:54,411 --> 00:41:54,879
Ouyang.

1048
00:41:55,279 --> 00:41:56,013
Sorry

1049
00:41:56,046 --> 00:41:57,281
to bother you so late.

1050
00:41:57,715 --> 00:41:58,282
It's okay.

1051
00:41:58,649 --> 00:41:59,483
What's the matter?

1052
00:42:00,184 --> 00:42:00,985
My mother-in-law

1053
00:42:01,318 --> 00:42:02,353
is hospitalized

1054
00:42:02,453 --> 00:42:03,787
in Dongli Cardiology.

1055
00:42:04,054 --> 00:42:05,489
The doctor said she has atrial fibrillation

1056
00:42:05,956 --> 00:42:07,725
and wants to perform

1057
00:42:08,492 --> 00:42:09,627
radiofrequency ablation

1058
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,762
and left atrial appendage closure

1059
00:42:11,929 --> 00:42:12,930
as a one-stop procedure.

1060
00:42:13,731 --> 00:42:15,032
A one-stop AF procedure?

1061
00:42:16,433 --> 00:42:18,002
Doesn't your mother-in-law want to take medication?

1062
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:19,670
The doctor said

1063
00:42:19,870 --> 00:42:21,405
the medication carries high risks.

1064
00:42:21,605 --> 00:42:23,307
But I looked online,

1065
00:42:23,908 --> 00:42:25,409
and it seems

1066
00:42:25,609 --> 00:42:27,011
the procedure is risky too.

1067
00:42:27,478 --> 00:42:28,545
Could you

1068
00:42:28,612 --> 00:42:29,747
send me

1069
00:42:29,813 --> 00:42:30,347
your mother-in-law's medical records?

1070
00:42:30,681 --> 00:42:31,515
Of course.

1071
00:42:31,715 --> 00:42:32,683
I'll send them now.

1072
00:42:33,083 --> 00:42:33,751
Sorry to trouble you.

1073
00:42:34,084 --> 00:42:34,752
Please take a look.

1074
00:42:35,286 --> 00:42:35,786
It's no trouble.

1075
00:42:36,754 --> 00:42:37,755
Okay, send them over.

1076
00:42:37,888 --> 00:42:38,322
Thank you.
